The White House Press Secretary, Robert Gibbs, addressed various topics during a press conference. He mentioned that the Department of Justice asked the US attorneys to stay and continue serving, with 51 out of 93 currently still serving. He also discussed the situation in Afghanistan, stating that the President ordered additional troops to address the deteriorating security situation and to prepare for the Taliban offensives and secure elections. Gibbs also talked about executive pay provisions in the stimulus package, emphasizing the need to ensure that executive compensation is not excessive and that regulations are in place. He mentioned that the administration will work with Congress to implement these provisions. Other topics discussed include the housing bill, the President's upcoming trip to Canada, and the status of the auto industry.